Fig. 8
 shows the fluorescent images of the W-CNPs at wavelengths of 405 nm and 488 nm. When incubated with these CNPs, 90% viable cardiomyocytes were seen after 6 h. 10% W-CNPs incubated cardiomyocytes showed spherical morphology with fewer extensions but exhibited the typical spindle morphology of cardiomyocytes after 24 h (Fig. 9
). Moreover, the cell viability was comparable to the control cells after 24 h indicating restoration of normal proliferation and cytocompatibility (Fig. 10
). As the average size of the W-CNPs was found to be 21 nm, it was internalized faster by the cardiomyocytes within 6 h of incubation as evidenced by the fluorescence intensity (Fig. 11
).
